steps.instruction:
## Owning data

The whole point of auth is that each user sees only their own data. You link todos to users with a **foreign key**:

```python
class Todo(db.Model):
    id = db.Column(db.Integer, primary_key=True)
    text = db.Column(db.String(200), nullable=False)
    done = db.Column(db.Boolean, default=False)
    user_id = db.Column(db.Integer, db.ForeignKey('user.id'), nullable=False)
```

`db.ForeignKey('user.id')` links each todo to the user who created it.

### Filtering by the current user

```python
@app.route('/')
@login_required
def index():
    todos = Todo.query.filter_by(user_id=current_user.id).order_by(Todo.id).all()
    return render_template('index.html', todos=todos, user=current_user)
```

### Saving with the user attached

```python
@app.route('/add', methods=['POST'])
@login_required
def add_todo():
    text = request.form['text']
    if text.strip():
        todo = Todo(text=text, user_id=current_user.id)
        db.session.add(todo)
        db.session.commit()
    return redirect(url_for('index'))
```

Now todos belong to users. User A can never see User B's todos.

